{"id": "720475", "revid": "1214363994", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki?curid=720475", "title": "Ljiljana Aran\u0111elovi\u0107", "text": "Ljiljana Aran\u0111elovi\u0107 (Serbian Cyrillic: \u0409\u0438\u0459\u0430\u043d\u0430 \u0410\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0452\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0438\u045b) (born 16 February 1963) is a Serbian politician and former presidential candidate in the 2004 Serbian presidential election.\nShe is a journalist and she has been an editor of many newspapers and RTV \u0106uprija.\nHer party, United Serbia, was created from the Party of Serbian Unity. She is its deputy president."}
